  "texts": [
    "These results show the necessity of model-specific defenses that consider model characteristics and threat type rather than a one-size-fits-all defense method.",
    "Remark 4: We reveal that the developed adaptive defenses are effective in counteracting PAP.",
    "Interestingly, they can also defend other types of jailbreak prompts beyond PAPs.",
    "This suggests that it is a worthwhile future direction to study the underlying connection between persuasion and jailbreak that aims to elicit compliance on prohibited topics.",
    "Additionally, we highlight the trade-off between safety and utility: while generalizable and effective defenses can enhance model safety, they can also diminish utility."
